The paper deals with the problem of feature disentanglement, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision. The use of variational autoencoders and supervised classification suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the mention of text analysis suggests that it may also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of auxiliary datasets and the focus on improving classification performance suggests that it may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
